<subSubSection pageId="203" pageNumber="204" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="203.[123,652,193,1389]" pageId="203" pageNumber="204">
REMARKS: This genus is closer to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Weber" authorityYear="1795" box="[554,651,751,774]" class="Malacostraca" family="Albuneidae" genus="Albunea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[554,651,751,774]" italics="true" pageId="203" pageNumber="204">Albunea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName box="[214,324,780,803]" class="Malacostraca" family="Albuneidae" genus="Lepidopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[214,324,780,803]" italics="true" pageId="203" pageNumber="204">Lepidopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and it is clearly a member of the 
<taxonomicName box="[211,348,809,832]" class="Malacostraca" family="Albuneidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Albuneinae">Albuneinae</taxonomicName>
, despite the presence of the 
<taxonomicName box="[177,294,839,862]" class="Malacostraca" family="Albuneidae" genus="Lepidopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[177,294,839,862]" italics="true" pageId="203" pageNumber="204">Lepidopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
­like anterolateral carapace spine. In fact, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hu and Tao" authorityYear="1996" box="[410,547,868,891]" class="Malacostraca" family="Albuneidae" genus="Paralbunea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[410,547,868,891]" italics="true" pageId="203" pageNumber="204">Paralbunea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closer to 
<taxonomicName box="[157,267,897,920]" class="Malacostraca" family="Albuneidae" genus="Lepidopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[157,267,897,920]" italics="true" pageId="203" pageNumber="204">Lepidopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than 
<taxonomicName box="[339,426,897,920]" class="Malacostraca" family="Albuneidae" genus="Zygopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[339,426,897,920]" italics="true" pageId="203" pageNumber="204">Zygopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is, and that genus has always been closely allied to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Weber" authorityYear="1795" box="[554,651,927,950]" class="Malacostraca" family="Albuneidae" genus="Albunea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[554,651,927,950]" italics="true" pageId="203" pageNumber="204">Albunea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Serene, R." box="[191,349,956,979]" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" pagination="95 - 99" refId="ref287676" refString="Serene, R. 1979. Description of Paralbunea manihinei gen. and spec. nov. (Decapoda, Hippidea, Albuneidae). Crustaceana, suppl. 5: 95 - 99, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1979">Serène, 1979</bibRefCitation>
). The sister taxon to 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Albuneidae" genus="Zygopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="203" pageNumber="204">Zygopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName authority="BOYKO, 2002" authorityName="BOYKO" authorityYear="2002" box="[211,372,985,1008]" class="Malacostraca" family="Albuneidae" genus="Squillalbunea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[211,372,985,1008]" italics="true" pageId="203" pageNumber="204">Squillalbunea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[392,478,985,1008]" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, which shares many characters with this genus, including a narrow anterior carapace margin with low rounded granules instead of acute spines, a rugose dorsal margin on the dactylus of pereopod I, and elongate, fully calcified male and female telsons. The two species of 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Albuneidae" genus="Zygopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="203" pageNumber="204">Zygopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are from opposite sides of the world, but are nevertheless extremely difficult to separate even when examined side by side. This suggests that little divergence has taken place within this genus, despite the duration and distance for which the species have been separated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
